"[REVIEW: untranslated]   shutdown the postmaster servicing the new cluster\n"

#: option.c:342
#, c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"When you run pg_upgrade, you must provide the following information:\n"
"  the data directory for the old cluster  (-d DATADIR)\n"
"  the data directory for the new cluster  (-D DATADIR)\n"
"  the \"bin\" directory for the old version (-b BINDIR)\n"
"  the \"bin\" directory for the new version (-B BINDIR)\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"[REVIEW: untranslated] When you run pg_upgrade, you must provide the following information:\n"
"[REVIEW: untranslated]   the data directory for the old cluster  (-d DATADIR)\n"
"[REVIEW: untranslated]   the data directory for the new cluster  (-D DATADIR)\n"
"[REVIEW: untranslated]   the \"bin\" directory for the old version (-b BINDIR)\n"
"[REVIEW: untranslated]   the \"bin\" directory for the new version (-B BINDIR)\n"

#: option.c:348
#, c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"For example:\n"
"  pg_upgrade -d oldCluster/data -D newCluster/data -b oldCluster/bin -B newCluster/bin\n"
"or\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"For example:\n"
"[REVIEW: untranslated]   pg_upgrade -d oldCluster/data -D newCluster/data -b oldCluster/bin -B newCluster/bin\n"
"or\n"

#: option.c:353
#, c-format
msgid ""
"  $ export PGDATAOLD=oldCluster/data\n"
"  $ export PGDATANEW=newCluster/data\n"
"  $ export PGBINOLD=oldCluster/bin\n"
"  $ export PGBINNEW=newCluster/bin\n"
"  $ pg_upgrade\n"
msgstr ""
"[REVIEW: untranslated]   $ export PGDATAOLD=oldCluster/data\n"
"[REVIEW: untranslated]   $ export PGDATANEW=newCluster/data\n"
"[REVIEW: untranslated]   $ export PGBINOLD=oldCluster/bin\n"
"[REVIEW: untranslated]   $ export PGBINNEW=newCluster/bin\n"
"  $ pg_upgrade\n"

#: option.c:359
